| **Primary CTA (transactional — for paid traffic)** | **Secondary / softer CTA** |
| --- | --- |
| Book a discovery call Tell us about your project Request a free CGI consultation Get in touch with the team | Let's talk See our work Chat to us Tell me more |

# **Brand rules for Claude to follow**

The following visual and typographic rules are drawn directly from the Image Foundry Brand Guidelines. Claude must apply these when building HTML landing pages or providing design direction.

## **Colour palette**

| **Name** | **Hex** | **RGB** | **Usage** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **IF Primary Pink** | #a60064 | 166, 0, 100 | Primary brand. CTAs, accents, section bands. |
| **IF Primary Blue** | #006680 | 0, 102, 128 | Secondary brand. Section bands, supporting elements. |
| **IF Primary Yellow** | #ecaa00 | 236, 170, 0 | Use sparingly. Accent only. Never backgrounds. |
| **IF Secondary Pink** | #e01783 | 224, 23, 131 | Max 10% usage alongside primary pink only. |
| **IF Secondary Blue** | #00a4c3 | 0, 164, 195 | Max 10% usage alongside primary blue only. |

## **Typography**

| **Headline font** | Barlow Condensed — bold/medium weight. ALL CAPS. Apply +100 letter-spacing (tracking) to all headlines. Available from Google Fonts. |
| --- | --- |
| **Body font** | Barlow Condensed — regular or medium weight. Sentence case for body text. |
| **Headline size** | Hero: 72–96px. Section headlines: 48–64px. Sub-headlines: 32–40px. Adjust for mobile breakpoints. |
| **Body size** | 18–20px for comfortable reading on landing pages. 16px minimum. |
| **Google Fonts import** | https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Barlow+Condensed — import weights: 400 (regular), 500 (medium), 700 (bold). |

## **Layout and visual approach**

- Full-bleed imagery wherever possible. The work must take up space — this is a visual studio.

- Use bold colour bands (IF Pink or IF Blue) for section separators and CTA zones.

- Clean whitespace around text. Typography breathes. Nothing feels cramped.

- The IF wireframe logo marque can be used as a subtle graphic device overlaid on imagery — the brand guidelines show this in use.

- Colour usage: approximately 90% primary colour, 10% secondary accent. Never use secondary colours on backgrounds.

- Dark hero overlays work well with light text on photography. Keep text legible — minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio.

- Mobile-first: the hero headline must work at 36–48px on mobile. Test the copy at mobile scale.

# **Live website observations — what Claude must match**

The following is drawn from a direct review of www.imagefoundry.co.uk. The landing pages must feel like they belong to this site — same energy, same confidence, same visual weight — while being more focused and conversion-optimised than the main site.

## **Homepage design — what it tells us**

| **Hero** | Full-viewport autoplay video montage of CGI work. Dark overlay. Large white headline text centred. The video does the selling immediately. Landing pages should replicate this impact — either with an autoplay video loop or a single full-bleed, high-resolution CGI still. |
| --- | --- |
| **Current hero headline** | "Smarter, Faster, Better CGI" — note this is mixed case (not all caps), demonstrating that headline casing is flexible in practice. Claude should prioritise readability over rigid all-caps when the headline has multiple words. |
| **Section labels** | Small ALL CAPS eyebrow text above section headlines throughout the site — e.g. 'IMAGE FOUNDRY - MANCHESTER', 'WHAT WE DO', 'OUR WORK', 'CASE STUDIES'. Use this pattern on the landing pages. |
| **Service structure** | The site now organises services into three clear pillars: IMAGE (CGI stills), VIDEO (animation, cinematic CGI), INTERACTIVE (VR, 360°, product configurators). Use this three-pillar structure when referencing services. |
| **AI / Labs section** | Image Foundry has an active AI Labs section showcasing: adding people to imagery using AI, dynamic stills (motion from single still), and CGI video with lifelike people. This is a genuine differentiator and should be referenced as part of what makes the studio forward-thinking. |
| **Footer CTA** | The footer uses 'Let's talk' — a warm, low-pressure relational CTA. Keep this as the softer secondary CTA throughout the landing pages. |
| **Whitepaper** | Image Foundry has produced a whitepaper: 'Our in-depth guide to marketing new-build property' — including visual marketing strategies, a cheat sheet to successful imagery, and real stats from home buyers. This is a strong lead magnet for the property audience and could be offered as an alternative CTA. |

## **Real clients from the portfolio — use these in case study copy**

The following named clients appear in the Image Foundry case studies. Claude should reference these where relevant rather than inventing placeholder names — they add genuine credibility:

| **Property clients** | **Product / brand clients** |
| --- | --- |
| Forshaws (Clippers Quay, Manchester) — landmark residential development Rippon Homes — research-led CGI for property brochures and social Sage Housing — immersive visualisations for affordable housing Vistry Partnerships North East — King Edwards Park development Priors Hill — site plan and exterior CGI St James' Quay — photomontage and exterior CGI Vivid — living room and kitchen CGI | Breville — kitchen appliance CGI Ideal Standard — brochure CGI for sanitary ware Geberit — sanitary solutions CGI Aqualisa — bathroom products partnership Croydex — bathroom CGI roomsets and products JELD-WEN — product CGI stills (doors/windows) Accora — specialist bed manufacturer lifestyle CGI Layla Sleep — mattress product CGI Austroflamm — luxury fireplace product CGI The Radiator Company — interactive product configurator Jim Beam — distillery marketing CGI |

## **Visual design language — what to replicate**

- Dark, immersive hero zones with light text. The site is confident and premium — the landing pages should match this energy.

- Clean white content sections with strong typographic hierarchy alternate with dark or brand-colour sections. The rhythm is: dark hero → white content → colour band → white content → colour CTA.

- Section eyebrow labels in small all-caps (e.g. 'CASE STUDIES', 'OUR PROCESS', 'WHAT WE DELIVER') precede every major headline.

- Imagery is always the dominant element. Text is clean, well-spaced, and never crowds the visuals.

- The IF logo mark (the geometric 'F' device) can be used as a subtle graphic element or watermark overlaid on imagery — as shown in the brand guidelines.

- Three-column grid is used for the Image / Video / Interactive service pillars. Use a similar grid for the three portfolio case studies.

- The site footer always shows the IF logo, 'Let's talk' CTA, and navigation — keep this structure on the landing page footer but strip it back to logo + CTA + contact details only.

# **Page specifications — what Claude should build**

## **Output format**

Claude should produce the following outputs for each page:

- A full HTML file with embedded CSS — production-ready, single-file, mobile responsive

- Barlow Condensed loaded from Google Fonts CDN (weights 400, 500, 700)

- Placeholder images and video referenced clearly, e.g. [HERO VIDEO — CGI montage from IF portfolio] or [HERO IMAGE — property exterior CGI]

- All copy written out in full — headlines, subheadlines, body copy, CTA text, case study descriptions, and testimonial placeholders

## **Page A — Property developer landing page**

| **Audience** | Property developers, development managers, and property marketing teams. Primarily targeting off-plan sales of residential and mixed-use developments. |
| --- | --- |
| **URL slug suggestion** | /property-cgi or /off-plan-cgi |
| **Hero visual** | Option A: Autoplay looping video montage of property CGI work (matching the homepage approach). Option B: Full-viewport still of a photorealistic residential exterior — golden hour, lifestyle props, people visible. Both should have a dark overlay with white headline text. |
| **Hero headline** | Write 3 options and recommend one. 5–8 words. Use Barlow Condensed. Outcome-led or transformation-framed. |
| **Primary CTA** | 'Tell us about your development' or 'Book a discovery call' — leads to a simple contact form: Name, Company, Phone, 'Tell us about your project'. |
| **Secondary CTA** | Consider offering the whitepaper as an alternative entry point: 'Download our guide to marketing new-build property' — lower commitment, builds trust first. |
| **Case studies** | Use real client names from the portfolio where possible: Forshaws / Clippers Quay, Rippon Homes, Sage Housing, Vistry, St James' Quay. Write 3 using the solved-problem formula. |
| **Services to reference** | Use the three-pillar structure: IMAGE (exterior/interior CGI, aerial, floor plans, photo montage), VIDEO (fly-through animation, dynamic stills), INTERACTIVE (360° tours, VR, site plan tools). |
| **AI differentiator** | Reference Image Foundry's AI capability for adding realistic people to property CGI — this is a current competitive edge and relevant to property marketing where lifestyle imagery sells. |

## **Page B — Product manufacturer landing page**

| **Audience** | Marketing and brand managers at KBB manufacturers (kitchen, bedroom, bathroom) and consumer product companies. |
| --- | --- |
| **URL slug suggestion** | /product-cgi or /product-visualisation |
| **Hero visual** | Full-viewport lifestyle CGI of a product in a beautifully staged environment — a kitchen, bathroom, or living space. Premium quality, photorealistic. Dark or light overlay depending on image tone. |
| **Hero headline** | Write 3 options and recommend one. Must acknowledge the photography alternative and position CGI as the smarter choice. |
| **Primary CTA** | 'Tell us about your product' or 'Book a free CGI consultation' — leads to a simple contact form. |
| **Case studies** | Use real client names: Breville, Ideal Standard, Geberit, Aqualisa, Croydex, JELD-WEN, Accora, Layla Sleep, Austroflamm. Pick 3 with variety across sectors. |
| **Services to reference** | IMAGE (product lifestyle CGI, cut-outs, pack shots, room sets, multiple colourways from a single 3D model), VIDEO (product animation, cinematic sequences), INTERACTIVE (product configurators, 360° views). |
| **Key proof point** | Emphasise: one 3D model → unlimited colourways, angles, and configurations. Faster and more cost-effective than photography at scale. Consistent quality across entire product ranges. |

